name: YUKON
description: This amazing pet qualifies for a reduced adoption fee as he/she has been in the shelter's care for four weeks or longer. This pet is eligible for adoption for $10, which includes the spay/neuter, initial vaccines and microchip identification. Please visit the shelter today to meet this beautiful pet and inquire about adoption!Yukon is a gentle and affectionate dog who loves nothing more than being by your side. He has a calm and relaxed demeanor, but he also has a playful side that comes out whenever he sees a rope or a squeaky toy.Hobbies: Loves long walks and playing tug-of-war with his rope and snuggling on the couch with his humans.  Loves a Kong with kibble and pumpkin.  Yukon make look big but he's a big softie at heart. All he wants is someone to love and play with.  Up-to-date on all vaccinations and has a clean bill of health.

description: This amazing pet qualifies for a reduced adoption fee as he/she has been in the shelter's care for four weeks or longer. name: SADIE
description: Sadie's (A464854) day out from the shelter brought her some much needed respite from the noise and commotion. I've heard she's been overlooked for some time, but I found this girl to be the sweetest angel. She easily jumped in the car and enjoyed the scenery passing by as she sat at the window. In the backyard she ran and played with the toy but mostly wanted interaction from me. She gets excited but easily calms when asked. Sadie rolled in the grass enjoying the warm sun and light breeze. I thought I saw a smile to thank me. This girl loves to give kisses once she feels safe next to you!She's an excellent long walker and greets everyone who passes. At lunch with us she was perfect so she was treated with a doggie custard cone from Andy's. After the sugar high she rested in the chair with me capturing all the smells coming her way. We couldn't let her return to the shelter without a pup cup from Starbucks-an extra big one for this well behaved special girl.I heard Sadie snoring while on our way back. I couldn't be more thrilled to see her so relaxed dreaming of the fun day she experienced.Sadie's been waiting for her loving home for quite awhile. Please come visit  and fall in love with this gentle beautiful girl.This amazing pet qualifies for a reduced adoption fee as he/she has been in the shelter's care for four weeks or longer. This pet is eligible for adoption for $10, which includes the spay/neuter, initial vaccines and microchip identification. Please visit the shelter today to meet this beautiful pet and inquire about adoption!

name: ZEUS
description: "Zeus (A545934) was my favorite buddy for a Doggie Day Out. As part of a confiscation and later an owner surrender this big boy has experienced life at its worst but somehow is still the sweetest fun loving dog. He may be a senior, but his zest for activity is strong. He walked without pulling for a couple miles around the neighborhood. Zeus is the best  walker since it was his walk I let him sniff along the way.When it comes to food he will pull but can you blame him as he's so thin.  A special feeding plan has been initiated for weight gain. All his energy was used to walk around the backyard, chew on a bone and take in the warm sun. He even got a bath so now he smells so good. Later a trip to Twistee Treat allowed him to have his very own ice cream made for dogs. The day would not be complete without a stop for a pupcup. Zeus was exhausted on his way back to the shelter as he curled up beside me and rested his head on my lap and I stroked him to sleep. Zeus, with his fun goofy demeanor, made me happy that he enjoyed the day I planned for him. Once Zeus decompresses in an adoptive home he will curl up by YOUR side with his head in YOUR lap. Let's get this sweet boy home for the holidays."DG

name: JOY
description: Volunteer Notes:  Meet  Joy!   She was left in one of the play yards here at OCAS, possibly thrown over the fence.  She is shy , scared of many things including the play structures, toys and even the kennel door.  She cowers and warms up slowly.

name: BAGHEERA
description: Great news! My heartworm treatment is sponsored, meaning much of the cost of my heartworm treatment will be covered! Adopt me today so I can begin my treatment.

name: Amora
description: Hello, my name is Amora. I have been told how beautiful I am, and I cannot deny that it's the truth:) I have been at PRBJ for over 6 years waiting for my forever home. I know that is a really long time, more than half of my life. I am a great girl just ask anyone at the rescue center. I need time to get to know a person and trust them, but once I do, I will love you forever. I never forget those that love me. I am a little older now and really would just like a home that I can relax with my human. I am good on the leash, but really don't like going too far...but maybe if I had a great person to walk me and keep me safe, I would enjoy walking. I DO NOT like other animals (cats, dogs, birds, squirrels, etc), so my ideal home would need to be pet-free.... although I think I wouldn't mind a fish. I DO NOT like new people, so I would need a home that only has 1-2 ADULTS ONLY with very limited traffic in order to keep me and them safe. Please don't let any of this discourage you from wanting to adopt me. I know the right person is out there and the staff at the center is willing to work with us to ensure I get to the right home. It will take time for you to come in and meet me a few times, but I can guarantee I am worth it.

name: Avie
description: Update from foster: She really is super sweet. Avie does best with someone who is home much of the time. Working from home would be great, if possible. She will need time to transition and build trust. We have several dogs in our house and with a slow introduction, Avie did very well with them. Avie was rescued off the street by a family who helped get her into a better living situation. She was very shy when she came in and even shied away from being petted or touched in any way. Now she is so happy to get her backend scratched and pet. She wags her little crooked tail and gives kisses. She is good with cats and good with kids. We were told that she did not get along with dogs but believe it was the other dogs not liking her because she has gone on pack walks with several other dogs and done great. She has even gone into a foster with dogs of various ages and size with no issues. Avie is good on leash. She is playful, loves her toys, and is potty and crate trained.

name: Bandita
description: Bandita was surrendered to PRBJ when her family was no longer able to care for her. She loves to be with her people and would do well with a person that worked from home or was home most of the time. Bandita was trained to use pee-pads, so new owners will need to be diligent and work on potty training outside. A fenced yard would be ideal for her. She does not seem to like cats, and we are not sure about dogs at this point. She has had limited exposure to kids, so are recommending an adult only or older teen home to ensure Bandita feels comfortable.

name: Bishop
description: Beautiful Bishop FKA Quiver was returned to PRBJ after almost 3 years with a family. Unfortunately, now that there was a toddler running around he was playing too roughly and chasing her. The family was concerned that the toddler could get injured accidentally. Bishop likes to go for walks and is great on the leash. He is dog friendly. Due to him being a strong pup that likes to play, we are recommending a home with older teens or no kids.

name: Catniss
description: Are you looking for the absolute sweetest dog with the bestest kisses ever? That’s me…..that’s me! I know that my beautiful face looks a little sad, but life has not been easy so far. I ended up in a kill shelter and wonderful Judy saved me and my two tiny babies. I have had a hard life. All I want is a home with people to love me and a nice, 6 foot high fenced backyard where I can sunbathe and romp around. I am not a fan of cats, sorry....kitties and me just do not mix, so I can't be in a home with cats. But, I do love, love, love people (including kids), riding in the car and I walk very nicely on leash, especially if we can walk for a long time. I go walking after I eat in the am... which is usually 6-6:30...and have 2 Poops...and only on my walks not in the yard. I am a perfect age....past all the puppy nonsense, but I still have lots of years left to play with you, go on adventures and just love the heck out of you!

name: Daphnie
description: Daphnie was surrendered to PRBJ when her family was unable to care for her due to her high energy and family not having the time to dedicate to her training. Daphnie is playful and loves her toys. She does well with (older) kids as she is energetic and strong. She is looking for an active owner or family. A fenced yard is preferred for this energetic pup. As a graduate of the training camp, DAPNHIE enjoyed time with a trainer and learned many basic canine skills. She would be a great addition for an active family!

name: Duke
description: Duke is a very sweet dog, who needs a quiet household. It takes him a while to become acclimated to new people. He is currently in a foster home with a wonderful man who came to visit him here at the shelter multiple times to spend some time with him before he was ready to take him home. Duke is very happy in his home and loves to explore the yard. He has discovered that Duke does not like to be left alone for very long. He does not tear things up or destroy anything, he just gets nervous and shakes when he's alone for an extended period of time. We would like his permanent home to have someone home most of the time (work from home or retired) to keep him company during the day. Since he does not do well meeting new people he should not be walked in a busy community where strangers might want to come up and pet him. He will either need a backyard where he can safely run and play or live somewhere there is minimal walking traffic.

name: Granger
description: Granger came to PRBJ after he was dumped, and a kind lady took him in and searched for the owner. He is a playful pup who enjoys playing with other dogs. Granger has beautiful Curr markings, and characteristic of the breed, is a strong boy. He is not used to being in a crate and will need leash training. Granger would prefer a home with older kids as he is energetic.

name: Josh
description: Josh came to PRBJ from the panhandle of FL. He was in a high kill shelter and made their way in search of their forever homes. He is a Feist mix, so they do have lots of energy and will need a home with an active family or person.

name: Kato
description: Kato is a happy dog who loves to chew on bones and enjoys spending time with his humans. He loves long walks and running around. Kato knows several commands such as sit and touch and loves being the center of attention. He needs to be the only dog in the home and requires a fenced-in backyard to run and play. Kato is a dominant and physically strong dog, requiring an experienced family who understands Siberian Huskies.

name: Little Man
description: Little Man made his way to PRBJ through the Pilots for Paws program to find his forever home. He bonds quickly with his owner and would do well with an experienced Shepherd/alpha breed owner. Little Man will need training and socialization to understand his role, as he tends to be protective. He is best suited for a home with limited traffic, without children, and with an active owner who can burn off his energy. He has been known to climb chain-link fences, so a secure environment is essential.

name: Mopar
description: Mopar is a strong and handsome dog who enjoys long walks, jogging, and hiking. He loves belly rubs and snuggling, but needs an experienced owner to help with his strength and protective instincts. Mopar is highly trainable and knows many commands. He is best suited for a single-owner household as he can be protective of his space. He enjoys outdoor activities, but can get upset around bicycles, requiring guidance to stay calm during walks.

name: Nick
description: Nick is a playful and friendly pup who loves walks and running in the yard. He needs a diligent owner to monitor his natural digging instincts and keep him supervised, especially when outside. Nick requires some training but is sure to be a wonderful companion for an active household. He was surrendered when his owner had to move out of state and could no longer care for him.

name: Raven
description: Raven is a sweet and loving dog who has been waiting for a home since 2019. She enjoys cuddling, watching TV, and has become very attached to her foster family. Raven is house-trained and would thrive in a home with a 6-foot fence. She has a moderate shedding amount and grooming needs are low. Raven is ready to find her forever home with someone who can appreciate her wonderful personality.

name: Sandee
description: Sandee is a sweet and playful dog who has been through a lot, including mistreatment in her previous home. She is house-trained and loves running around. Sandee would do best in a low-traffic household without children or other pets. She enjoys being scratched on the sides of her neck, loves her treats, and is quick to learn commands like sit, shake, stay, and down. A fenced backyard is essential for her to safely play and enjoy her time outside.

name: Sunkist
description: Sunkist is a sweet dog who was surrendered to PRBJ along with her 9 puppies after being abandoned by her owner. She is a little nervous due to all the changes in her life, but once she warms up, her loving nature shines through. Sunkist would do best in a quieter environment where she can feel secure and thrive. She is house-trained and in need of some obedience training.

name: Sweetie Pie
description: Sweetie Pie is an energetic and playful dog who loves her humans. She enjoys playing with easy-going, non-aggressive dogs and has formed bonds with others at the rescue, such as KitKat and Moose. Sweetie Pie would thrive in a home with a 6-foot fenced backyard where she can burn off her energy. She can also be a great helper in the garden, as she loves digging holes. She is house-trained and in need of further obedience training.

name: Wallace
description: Wallace, also known as Wally, is a friendly and gentle Treeing Walker Coonhound. He graduated from a 10-week training camp and has an excellent leash manner. Wallace is great with humans, big and small, other dogs, and cats. He enjoys a quiet home and would love a family that works from home or is retired. He needs a 6-foot secured fenced yard and monitoring while outdoors. Wallace is a social butterfly who enjoys making new friends and has a lovely, calm personality.

name: Calia
description: Calia is a relaxed and independent Brown Tabby with white markings. She is playful but tends to keep to herself. Calia was surrendered to PRBJ when her previous owner could no longer care for her. She is housetrained and is good with other cats and kids. Calia enjoys her own space but is affectionate in her own way.

name: Callie
description: Callie is a friendly, FIV+ calico cat who enjoys looking out windows and basking in the sun. She was surrendered to PRBJ after her owner could no longer take care of her. Callie lived with her previous owner for 7 years and is housetrained. Despite her condition, she can live a normal, happy life. Callie is seeking a home where she can relax and enjoy her golden years.

name: Cardinal
description: Cardinal is a friendly 9-month-old black kitten who was found in a backyard with his siblings after their mother went missing. He was cared for by a family until they were able to bring him to PRBJ. Cardinal is housetrained and ready to find his forever home.

name: Cinder
description: Cinder is a playful and sweet 3-month-old brown tabby kitten who was found without her mother along with her siblings. After receiving care and nourishment at PRBJ, she is now ready for adoption. Cinder is housetrained and friendly, looking for her forever home.

name: Ember
description: Ember is a playful and sweet 3-month-old brown tabby kitten who was found without her mother along with her siblings. After receiving care and nourishment at PRBJ, she is now ready for adoption. Ember is housetrained and friendly, looking for her forever home.

name: Inferno
description: Inferno is a playful and sweet 3-month-old black tabby kitten who was found without his mother, along with his siblings. After receiving care and nourishment at PRBJ, he is now ready for adoption. Inferno is housetrained, friendly, and looking for a forever home.

name: Jack-Jack
description: Jack-Jack is a playful and affectionate Domestic Medium Hair who loves attention. He and his companion, Calia, were surrendered to PRBJ by their owner who could no longer care for them. Jack-Jack enjoys being the center of attention and is always ready to play!

name: Jackson
description: Jackson is a sweet and friendly Brown Tabby who was found alone outdoors. He was taken in by a kind lady who had him vaccinated and neutered, but due to her older cats not accepting him, he was brought to PRBJ to find his forever home. Jackson is ready to bring joy to a new family!

name: Leeward
description: Leeward is a sweet and affectionate black Manx cat who was abandoned by his owners and left in a flooded bathroom at a warehouse. Thankfully, he and his companion, Harriett, were discovered just in time. Leeward is a love bug who enjoys being brushed and would be a great addition to a home looking for an affectionate cat. He doesn’t need to be adopted with Harriett, but being adopted together would help him feel more comfortable.

name: Lelia
description: Lelia is a beautiful white cat with striking black markings. She and her companion, Shibu, were surrendered to PRBJ when their family had to move and could no longer keep them. Lelia is friendly and enjoys the company of others. She is housetrained, microchipped, and has a moderate shedding amount.

name: Maverick
description: Maverick is a resilient little kitten who was found near an apartment complex when he was just 1-2 days old. After being bottle-fed and cared for, he grew into a playful, loving kitty. Though he was fostered in a home with dogs, he never had full interaction with them. He is now looking for his forever home.

name: Neo
description: Neo was found by a kind person who gave him a safe space and took him to the vet. Unfortunately, they were unable to keep him, but now he’s a playful kitten looking for his forever home.

name: Rumba
description: Rumba is one of six orange kitties found in a yard when they were about 4 weeks old. After caring for them until they were old enough for vaccines, she is now ready for adoption. She would love to be adopted with a sibling or to join a home with another young cat. She prefers a home without dogs.

name: Shibu
description: Shibu and his companion, Lelia, were surrendered to PRBJ when their family had to move and could no longer care for them. Shibu is a sweet long-haired boy who would love to find his forever home.

name: Sydney
description: Sydney was adopted from PRBJ earlier this year but was returned through no fault of his own due to his owner's allergies. He is a sweet, playful, and loving cat who is looking for a forever home.

name: Tabasco
description: Tabasco and his siblings were found by a little girl in the yard at her grandfather's house. After ensuring their safety from wildlife and heat, they were brought to PRBJ for care and TLC.

name: Tango
description: Tango and his siblings were found by a nice man in his yard at around 4 weeks old. After the mother didn't return, they were cared for until ready for adoption. Tango is seeking a home with another young cat and no dogs.

name: Valentina
description: Valentina and her siblings from the hot sauce litter were found by a little girl in the yard at her grandfather's house. After ensuring their safety from wildlife and the heat, they were brought to PRBJ for care and TLC.

name: Vitani
description: Vitani was found near a feral colony, seemingly friendly and hungry. She was brought to PRBJ for care and is friendly and playful with other cats.

name: Waltz
description: Waltz and his siblings were found at around 4 weeks old in a yard by a kind man. After ensuring their safety and providing care, they were brought to PRBJ for vaccines and preparation for adoption. Waltz is looking for a home with another young cat or a sibling.

name: Carlisle
description: Hello, my name is Carlisle, I am young, sweet, and some consider me curious. I may look around my new home at first but call my name and I'll run over to give and receive all the love my new home has to provide. My hobbies are being petted and held, I am the best cuddler in the neighborhood! I am already neutered and of course I have all my rounds of shots. In addition to all first-year shots and neuter, I come with a registered microchip and a full set of medical records. If you are interested in meeting me, please complete an adoption application. Upon pre-approval, someone will reach out to set up a time for you to come meet me!

name: Charlene
description: Hi, I'm Charlene! I'm a fancy, black and white medium-hair kitten with a big black mustache, lol. I'm a sweet girl who likes to have fun. I love playing and watching cool cat shows on tv. I've had all of my first year shots and have been neutered- this is included in my adoption fee. You will just have to take me to get established at my new vet within 30 days of adopting me. If you are interested in meeting me, please complete an adoption application. Upon pre-approval, someone will reach out to set up a time for you to come meet me! In addition to all first-year shots and my neuter, I have a registered microchip and a full set of medical records. Since kittens do best with having playmates and someone to cuddle with when our people aren't around, I will have to go to a home with other cats or kittens or even a dog (who likes cats of course). Or you could adopt a second kitten from Second Chance, at a greatly reduced adoption fee.

name: Charlie
description: Hi, I'm Charlie. I'm a cuddly little guy! I've had a few sets of shots, just waiting to be big enough to go get neutered and get my rabies vaccine. name: Ed
description: Hi, I'm Ed. I've been at Second Chance for over 2 years now. I am a young, energetic, sweet boy. Did I say energetic? I love to go outside and play, or take walks. If you are looking for the adventurous type for hikes and outdoorsy fun, I'm your guy! I'm a little dog and people selective, I do best with female dogs and will do best with a confident and experienced dog owner. Also, no DNA tests have been done, so no one knows for sure what breed I am. I look like I might have Catahoula Leopard Dog in my mix and probably some bully. This means home ownership to adopt me is required! I have all had all of my shots, and am neutered. description: Hi, I'm Georgie. I have been at the rescue for over 2 years. I'm not sure why I've been overlooked, but I am a great dog! I love to go outside and play, or take walks. I also love to play with other dogs. I especially like car rides and going places. I am also very well behaved in public. No DNA tests have been done, so no one knows for sure what breed I am. name: Jack Jack
description: Hello, my name is Jack Jack, I am on the fluffier side so I am super soft you have no idea. I want to start by saying it isn't easy to look this handsome and be 20 pounds. I might be chunky but I am working on it, don't judge, I have my diet and of course my favorite exercise: Belly Rubs. I try to get at least one set a day mandatory. I am super sweet, with anyone and anything, I just really love my workout sets. I am already neutered and of course I have all my rounds of shots. In addition to all first-year shots and neuter, I come with a registered microchip and a full set of medical records. If you are interested in meeting me, please complete an adoption application. Upon pre-approval, someone will reach out to set up a time for you to come meet us!

name: Jackson
description: Hi! I'm Jackson. I am very shy and just a tiny bit scared of my own shawdow, why does it keep following me? Anyways, I warm up with time and understanding, I am very smart and know the command sit. I'm housebroken and crate trained, and overall a very good boy. I have great manners if I say so myself. I would do best in a household with no cats and no children under 13. I can be a bit dog-selective. I will need pawrents who understand that I am shy and busy/loud environments make me very nervous. I will thrive in a stable environment, with a yard of my own. Walks are fine from time to time, but sometimes loud noises, falling leaves, or something out of place, like a repair van, make walks for me a bit stressful. Therefore, a fenced-in yard will be required to adopt me. I've had all my shots, I've been neutered, and am ready to go home. I also come with a registered microchip and a full set of medical records (one copy for you and one for my new vet). If you are interested in meeting me, please complete an adoption application online. Upon pre-approval, someone will reach out to set up a time for you to come meet me. Requirements to adopt me: - Adopter must be 25 years or older - Must own home, no renters - Must have a fenced-in yard - No children in the home under 13 years old

name: Marilyn Monroe
description: Hiya! My name is Marilyn Monroe! Named after the glamorous actress and model, I've got a little beauty mark (a black speck of fur) that gives me a touch of Hollywood flair. I'm a super playful kitten who loves to chase and explore. I have a sister who shares my zest for life, and together we make a dynamic duo. If you're looking for a pretty, lively companion with a hint of star power, I'm here and ready to steal your heart! name: Peppermint Patty
description: Hi, my name is Peppermint Patty. Some call me Peppy for short. I am super smart, I already know sit, boop, down, drop it, wait, and leave it. I also know what they mean when they tell me to pee or poop on a walk, these are just the beginnings of words that I am learning, and I can (and want to) learn so much more! My favorite afternoon past-time is laying in the sun soaking up the rays (although this is Florida, so that only lasts about 10 minutes). I would benefit most from a home with someone VERY active and would like to take the time to train me on many more commands. The sky is the limit as to what I can learn. I do get along with other dogs (with slow introductions), but I am also very intense, so it depends on whether the other dog is willing and able to set boundaries for me. I require slow introductions to people as well, you can't just trust everyone. Since I am young, and strong, it would be best to be in a home without children. I love to go on walks, but love yard zoomies as well, so a fenced-in yard is preferred. I am a bit of a handful, so we don't want anyone to think they are entering into this lightly with me. I will need love, time and lots of training to be the best dog I can be. In return, you will have my loyalty and love, I'm a very wonderful companion. No DNA tests have been done, but since Cattle Dog and possibly Blue Nose Pit are both on the restricted breed list, homeownership is required to adopt me. No renters. I have all had all of my shots, and am spayed. This is all included in my adoption fee, as well as a registered microchip and a full set of medical records for you and my future vet! If you are interested in meeting me, please complete an adoption application. Upon pre-approval, someone will reach out to set up a time for a meet and greet. I'm looking forward to meeting you! Only applicants who meet the following current requirements will be considered: - Homeownership, no renters - Children in the home must be 13 and up - Fenced yard not required, but preferred

Heads up, I am special needs because I am FIV positive. I can live very amicably with other cats and kittens, the only thing is, I'm more susceptible to getting sick. Here at Second Chance, they help me boost my immune system by sprinkling L-Lysine on my food, so overall, I'm a pretty healthy and totally sweet guy!
